banks, thus future tarring of the Sani Pass may result in an increase of exotic species richness and abundance. This would initially result from construction-related soil disturbance and subsequently from increased traffic, water run-off, and altered fire frequency. We suggest examples of management actions to prevent this.", "access_right": "restricted", "creators": [{"name": "Kalwij, Jesse M.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Robertson, Mark P.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "van Rensburg, Berndt J.", "affiliation": null}], "keywords": ["Chapter 2", "biodiversity", "environment assessment", "IPBES", "Alien Invasive Species Assessment AIS", "invasive species"], "related_identifiers": [{"identifier": "hash://md5/ea43af1b1f8bafdb5630d91254cb67f8", "relation": "hasVersion", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "hash://sha256/c4c3ca362a125bb0dd72ed68ac729367bd448284cf3b1065b51d098f83318235", "relation": "hasVersion", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "zotero://select/groups/2352922/items/PI9NY5GF", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "https://zotero.org/groups/2352922/items/PI9NY5GF", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "https://linker.bio/cut:hash://md5/6f5ffc7849d46604da7c0a2a9ff5033c!/b51497-53995", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "hash://md5/359bd494433933b868f85e88d3437f76", "relation": "isPartOf", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "10.3170/2008-7-18555", "relation": "isVariantFormOf", "resource_type": "publication", "scheme": "doi"}, {"identifier": "10.5281/zenodo.7430682", "relation": "isCitedBy", "resource_type": "publication-report", "scheme": "doi"}, {"identifier": "10.5281/zenodo.1410543", "relation": "isCompiledBy", "resource_type": "software", "scheme": "doi"}], "resource_type": {"title": "Journal article", "type": "publication", "subtype": "article"}, "journal": {"issue": "4", "pages": "491-498", "title": "Applied Vegetation Science", "volume": "11"}, "alternate_identifiers": [{